  "title": "FOOT REFLEXOLOGIST",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Treatment Delivery:</strong> Perform specialized reflexology, and often shoulder/hand, massages using thumbs and fingers to stimulate specific reflex zones.</li><li><strong>Client Consultation:</strong> Assess client needs, discuss medical conditions, and explain the benefits of the treatment.</li><li><strong>Hygiene & Safety:</strong> Clean and sanitize work areas, sterilize tools, and replace linens between clients.</li><li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Maintain accurate client records and treatment notes.</li><li><strong>Customer Service:</strong> Build rapport, address customer inquiries, and ensure a professional, comfortable experience. </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Skills:</strong> Proficiency in reflexology techniques, good communication, and strong, steady hands.</li><li><strong>Experience:</strong> Often requires 1–3 years of experience, though training is sometimes provided.</li><li><strong>Attributes:</strong> Pleasant, friendly, and professional disposition.</li><li><strong>Flexibility:</strong> Willingness to work weekends, evenings, and public holidays. </li></ul>",
